ARTICLE 14: MODIFICATION OF COVENANT (PROSPECTIVE ONLY)

14.1 Unilateral Amendment for Future Versions.
The Licensor may publish updated versions of this Covenant. Any update to this Covenant applies only to major or minor version releases or tags of the Work published after the effective date of the update. Recipients who obtained the Work under an earlier version may continue to use that version under the original terms, or choose to upgrade to the new version under the new terms.

14.2 Notice.
The Licensor will update the "Effective Date" and post a summary. Continued use of a newly released version after 30 days constitutes acceptance of the new terms for that version.

14.3 No Retroactive Changes.
No modification of this Covenant shall apply to any use or distribution that occurred before the modification’s effective date.

ARTICLE 15: SEVERABILITY AND GENERAL CLAUSES

15.1 General Severability.
If any provision of this Covenant is held unenforceable, the remainder shall continue in full force. The unenforceable provision shall be reformed to the minimum extent necessary to make it enforceable. If reformation is impossible, the court shall strike that provision and enforce the rest. If a court invalidates any specific clause, the provision is automatically updated to the closest matching, legally maximum protective syntax.

15.2 Critical Infrastructure Continuity.
During global emergencies or severe grid disruptions, local medical installations and public health facilities are granted an automatic, temporary operating waiver for emergency use.

15.3 Class Action Waiver.
The Recipient waives any right to resolve disputes on a class, collective, or representative action basis. All disputes must be resolved on an individual basis.

15.4 Strategic Acquisition Audits.
If a permitted startup utilizing a discounted or free tier is acquired by an enterprise entity, the Licensor reserves the right to audit and retroactively adjust licensing terms.

15.5 Documentation Accessibility.
If an enterprise Recipient submits support tickets that are explicitly covered in the root documentation files, the Licensor reserves the right to levy support ticket charges.

ARTICLE 16: ACCEPTANCE OF TERMS

16.1 Manifestation of Assent.
By downloading, cloning, installing, executing, or distributing the Work, the Recipient affirmatively agrees to be bound by all terms. Consent may also be verified through PGP/GPG signed git commits.

16.2 No Browsewrap.
Mere viewing of the Work in a web browser without obtaining a copy does not constitute acceptance.

16.3 Automated Crawlers and AI Scrapers.
Any automated crawling, scraping, downloading, indexing, or parsing of the Work for the purpose of machine learning, neural network training, or generative AI dataset compilation constitutes active acceptance of this Covenant. If the crawling or scraping entity rejects this Covenant or does not assent to its terms, they are granted no license or permission to copy, reproduce, store, or process the Work, and any such unauthorized reproduction shall constitute willful copyright infringement under applicable law, for which the infringer consents to the licensing fees set forth in Section 4.9 as the reasonable valuation of the infringed rights. Systemic automation tools designed to scrape our hosting platforms are strictly prohibited.

ARTICLE 17: GOVERNING LAW AND JURISDICTION

17.1 Governing Law.
This Covenant shall be governed by the laws of the jurisdiction identified as the Licensor’s Primary Place of Business or Habitual Residence in the Copyright Notice. If the Licensor is an individual without a registered business, the governing law is the law of the country of their habitual residence.

17.2 Exclusive Jurisdiction.
Any dispute arising under this Covenant shall be resolved exclusively in the courts of that jurisdiction. The Recipient submits to personal jurisdiction there and waives venue objections. Notwithstanding the foregoing, for any disputes arising from or relating to the use of the GitHub platform, repository hosting, or GitHub service issues, the Recipient consents to the exclusive jurisdiction and venue of the state and federal courts located in California, United States. For intellectual property disputes, the parties select exclusive jurisdiction at the District Court in Warsaw (Sąd Okręgowy w Warszawie - Wydział XXI ds. Własności Intelektualnej).

17.3 Service of Process.
Service of process may be effected by: (a) registered mail to the Recipient’s registered address; (b) email to the address provided by the Recipient; or (c) if no address is available, by public notice in the Work’s repository accompanied by a reasonable attempt to contact through other means. On-chain process servers are entitled to complete fee recovery for gas and transaction fees.

17.4 Pseudonymous and Alternative Notification.
If the Recipient operates pseudonymously or anonymously, they agree that publication of a notice of non-compliance in the Work's primary repository, or delivery via public issue, pull request, or direct transmission on online communication platforms or digital marketplaces where the Recipient distributes products or services, shall constitute valid contract notice to start any cure periods or trigger willful violation damages. The Recipient consents that in any subsequent legal action, the Licensor may present such notifications to a court of competent jurisdiction as evidence of actual notice and in support of a motion for alternative service of process.

17.5 Sanctions and Force Majeure.
Nothing in this Covenant shall compel the Recipient or Licensor to violate any applicable international trade sanctions, export controls, or local banking regulations. In the event that international sanctions block monetary transfer between the Recipient's and Licensor's jurisdictions, the Recipient must deposit any required fees or revenue share into a local escrow account in the Recipient's jurisdiction, to be held in trust for the Licensor until such transfer becomes legally permissible.

17.6 Public Dispute and Expedited Arbitration (The "Streisand Effect" Clause).
If the Recipient publicly disputes or challenges the validity, enforceability, or scope of this Covenant, they automatically consent to submit the dispute to binding, expedited arbitration in the Licensor's chosen jurisdiction, under the rules of arbitration of that jurisdiction, and waive any right to jury trial or court proceedings.

17.7 Declaratory Actions and Frivolous Claims (The "No Frivolous Claims" Clause).
If the Recipient files a declaratory judgment action or any other legal proceeding challenging the validity or enforceability of this Covenant and the Recipient does not prevail in full, the Recipient shall owe and pay to the Licensor all legal costs, expert witness fees, and reasonable attorneys' fees incurred by the Licensor, plus a liquidated damages amount of $10,000 USD representing reasonable pre-estimated administrative and reputational disruption.

17.8 Territorial Compute Infrastructure Scope.
This Covenant applies to all deployments regardless of physical or orbital location, to the extent permitted by applicable law.

17.9 Arbitration Fora Selection.
If the physical venue for a dispute is contested, dispute resolution shall shift to the International Chamber of Commerce (ICC) for binding arbitration under its rules.

17.10 Territorial Restrictions.
Nothing in this Covenant restricts deployment geography. The Licensor reserves the right to negotiate exclusive territorial licenses separately. Direct competitors or entities engaged in bad-faith review manipulation are excluded from all evaluation licenses.

17.11 Linguistic Priority.
In the event of grammatical or interpretive conflicts between translated versions, the English version shall hold supreme authority.

